{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi0 [!NOTE] {\b Tested on macOS Tahoe 26.2.} Windows and Linux support is expected but not yet verified. Contributions and feedback from other platforms are welcome!\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 What is ReaMD?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 ReaMD is a {\b dockable markdown viewer} designed specifically for audio production workflows in REAPER. It bridges the gap between your scripts, notes, and the timeline - allowing you to link text fragments directly to items on your tracks.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Perfect for:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Voiceover production} - Link script lines to VO recordings\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Audio post-production} - Sync scene descriptions with sound design\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Podcast editing} - Follow show notes while editing\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Music production} - Keep lyrics and arrangement notes in view\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Features\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Core Markdown Support\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Full markdown rendering (headers, lists, tables, code blocks, blockquotes)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Edit mode} - Write and modify markdown directly in REAPER\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Dark & Light themes} - Seamlessly match your REAPER theme\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Dockable window - Integrate into your workflow\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Scenario Linking\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Link text fragments to timeline items} - Click a paragraph, jump to the item\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Multi-item support} - One fragment can reference multiple items\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Category colors} - V (Voiceover), M (Music), F (FX), O (Other)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Group awareness} - REAPER item groups treated as single units\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Visual feedback} - Linked fragments highlighted, playback position tracked\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Teleprompter Mode\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b VO-focused display} - Shows only voiceover text, large and centered\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Auto-scroll} - Follows playback position automatically\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Progress indicator} - Orange (next cue) / Green (current item ending)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Semi-transparent overlay} - 50% opacity, stays out of the way\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 AI Parse (Claude Integration)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Paste unformatted text} - Meeting notes, raw scripts, brain dumps\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b AI formats to markdown} - Clean structure with proper headings and lists\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Customizable prompt} - Tailor the AI behavior to your workflow\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Non-blocking} - Async processing, UI stays responsive\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Installation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Requirements\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 | Component | Version | Required | |-----------|---------|----------| | REAPER | 7.0+ | Yes | | ReaImGui | 0.10+ | Yes | | js_ReaScriptAPI | Latest | Recommended | | SWS Extension | Latest | Recommended |\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Method 1: ReaPack (Recommended)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab {\b Add ReaMD repository to ReaPack:}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Open REAPER \u8594 ? Extensions \u8594 ? ReaPack \u8594 ? Import repositories...\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Paste: {\f1 https://github.com/b451c/ReaMD/raw/main/index.xml}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Click OK\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab {\b Install ReaMD:}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Extensions \u8594 ? ReaPack \u8594 ? Browse packages\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Search for "ReaMD" \u8594 ? Right-click \u8594 ? Install\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Apply and restart REAPER\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab {\b Run:}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Actions \u8594 ? Show action list\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Search for "ReaMD"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Double-click to run (or assign shortcut)\sa180\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Method 2: Manual Install\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab {\b Download} the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/b451c/ReaMD/releases/latest"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
latest release
}}}
 or clone:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi0 \f1 git clone https://github.com/b451c/ReaMD.git\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab {\b Copy to REAPER Scripts folder:}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi0 \f1 Windows: %APPDATA%\\REAPER\\Scripts\\ReaMD\\\line
macOS:   ~/Library/Application Support/REAPER/Scripts/ReaMD/\line
Linux:   ~/.config/REAPER/Scripts/ReaMD/\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab {\b Load the script:}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab REAPER \u8594 ? Actions \u8594 ? Load ReaScript\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Select {\f1 Main/ReaMD.lua}\sa180\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi0 {\b Tip:} For full functionality, install {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/cfillion/reaimgui"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
ReaImGui
}}}
, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://forum.cockos.com/showthread.php?t=212174"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
js_ReaScriptAPI
}}}
, and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.sws-extension.org/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
SWS Extension
}}}
.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Usage\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Basic Workflow\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab {\b Open a markdown file} - Click "Open..." or drag & drop\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab {\b Dock the window} - Right-click title bar \u8594 ? Dock\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab {\b Browse your script} - Scroll, search, navigate headings\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Scenario Linking\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab {\b Enter Scenario Mode} - Toggle "Scenario" in toolbar\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab {\b Select items on timeline} - The items you want to link\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab {\b Click [+] on a text fragment} - Links selected items to that text\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab {\b Click linked text} - Jumps to and selects the items\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab {\b Play} - Text highlights follow playback position\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Teleprompter\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab {\b Set up scenario links} - At least link your VO items\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab {\b Click "Teleprompter"} - Opens focused display window\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab {\b Start playback} - Text auto-scrolls with timeline\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 AI Parse\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Transform unstructured text into clean markdown using Claude AI.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Setup\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Get an API key from {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://console.anthropic.com/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
Anthropic Console
}}}
\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab In ReaMD, open {\b Settings} (gear icon)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Paste your API key in the "AI Parser Settings" section\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Usage\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Click {\b New \u8594 ? AI Parse...}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Paste your unformatted text\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Click {\b Parse with AI}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Review the result \u8594 ? {\b Save As...}\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Customize the Prompt\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Click {\b Edit Prompt} in settings to modify {\f1 prompts/ai_format_prompt.txt}. Tailor it for your specific use case (voiceover scripts, technical docs, meeting notes, etc.).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi0 {\b Note:} AI Parse requires an internet connection and uses the Claude Haiku model for fast, cost-effective processing.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
